l age of the source between 170 and 106 Myr, in agreement with the buoyancy\nand sound crossing time-scales derived from X-ray data. We then reconstructed\nthe duty cycle of the source. There were three phases of jet activity, with the\nAGN being active for most of the time with only brief quiescent phases,\nensuring the repeated heating of the central gas. Finally, energetic estimates\nrevealed that a source of additional pressure support must be present to\nsustain the bubbles against the pressure of the external medium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Apr 2021 18:00:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 May 2021 18:00:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-30"}
