{"id":"2104.08475","submitter":"Menahem Krief","authors":"Menahem Krief","title":"Analytic solutions of the nonlinear radiation diffusion equation with an\n  instantaneous point source in non-homogeneous media","comments":"The following article has been accepted for publication in Physics of\n  Fluids","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1063/5.0050422","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.flu-dyn astro-ph.HE physics.comp-ph physics.plasm-ph","license":"http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/","abstract":"  Analytic solutions to the nonlinear radiation diffusion equation with an\ninstantaneous point source for a non-homogeneous medium with a power law\nspatial density profile, are presented. The solutions are a generalization of\nthe well known solutions for a homogeneous medium. It is shown that the\nsolutions take various qualitatively different forms according to the value of\nthe spatial exponent. These different forms are studied in detail for linear\nand non linear heat conduction. In addition, by inspecting the generalized\nsolutions, we show that there exist values of the spatial exponent such the\nconduction front has constant speed or even accelerates. Finally, the various\nsolution forms are compared in detail to numerical simulations, and a good\nagreement is achieved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 17 Apr 2021 07:42:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-02"}
